# Simple Vectorless RAG with PageIndex + OpenRouter

This notebook replicates the [PageIndex simple RAG cookbook](https://github.com/VectifyAI/PageIndex/blob/main/cookbook/pageindex_RAG_simple.ipynb) but replaces the OpenAI LLM with any model available on **[OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai)**.

**How it works:**
1. Upload a PDF to PageIndex → get a hierarchical tree index ("table of contents")
2. Use an OpenRouter LLM to **reason over the tree** and select the relevant node IDs
3. PageIndex retrieves the text for those nodes
4. Use the same OpenRouter LLM to **generate the final answer** from the retrieved context

> ⚡ OpenRouter exposes an OpenAI-compatible API, so the only change from the original notebook is pointing the OpenAI client at `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1` and using your OpenRouter API key + model name.
## 0. Setup
%pip install -q --upgrade pageindex openai requests
### 0.1 Configure API keys and model
import os

# --- PageIndex ---
# Get your free API key at https://dash.pageindex.ai/api-keys
PAGEINDEX_API_KEY = os.getenv("PAGEINDEX_API_KEY", "YOUR_PAGEINDEX_API_KEY")

# --- OpenRouter ---
# Get your API key at https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY = os.getenv("OPENROUTER_API_KEY", "YOUR_OPENROUTER_API_KEY")

# Choose any model from https://openrouter.ai/models
# Examples:
#   "openai/gpt-4o"                          (OpenAI via OpenRouter)
#   "anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet"            (Anthropic via OpenRouter)
#   "google/gemini-2.0-flash-001"            (Google via OpenRouter)
#   "meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct"      (Meta open model)
#   "mistralai/mistral-small-3.1-24b-instruct" (Mistral)
#   "deepseek/deepseek-r1"                   (DeepSeek R1)
OPENROUTER_MODEL = "google/gemini-2.0-flash-001"
### 0.2 Initialise PageIndex client
from pageindex import PageIndexClient
import pageindex.utils as utils

pi_client = PageIndexClient(api_key=PAGEINDEX_API_KEY)
### 0.3 Initialise OpenRouter LLM client

OpenRouter is OpenAI-API-compatible, so we just point the `openai` library at OpenRouter's base URL.
from openai import AsyncOpenAI

llm_client = AsyncOpenAI(
    api_key=OPENROUTER_API_KEY,
    base_url="https://openrouter.ai/api/v1",
)

print(f"LLM model: {OPENROUTER_MODEL}")
