## 6. Switching models

One of the key benefits of OpenRouter is being able to swap models with a single line change.
The cell below shows how to run the same query with a different model.
# Temporarily override the model for comparison
original_model = OPENROUTER_MODEL
OPENROUTER_MODEL = "meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct"  # swap here

await pageindex_rag(
    "Summarise the main contributions of this paper in 3 bullet points.",
    doc_id,
    tree,
)

OPENROUTER_MODEL = original_model  # restore
---

## Summary

This notebook demonstrated **vectorless, reasoning-based RAG** with PageIndex, powered by an **OpenRouter LLM**.

The key changes vs the original PageIndex cookbook:

| | Original | This notebook |
|---|---|---|
| LLM provider | OpenAI directly | **OpenRouter** (any model) |
| `base_url` | `https://api.openai.com/v1` | `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1` |
| API key | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | **`OPENROUTER_API_KEY`** |
| Model | `gpt-4.1` | **any OpenRouter model** |
| Retrieval | `PageIndexClient` | unchanged |

Because OpenRouter is OpenAI-compatible, **no other code changes are needed**.

